Do you train alone? If so, give this style of exercise a try.

In my opinion, training alone has one downfall... How do you push yourself when no one is watching?

That's why I started doing exercises like this and recording my times. It helps me always be better then the guy I was yesterday. It's me vs me.

Instead of the mirror, I look over my progress. When I can see clear strength gains, I get motivated to keep grinding.

Give it a shot. If 100 reps is too much, try 50. Or modify the workout, use a resistance band, etc. There's always a way to scale it to your level.
